tldr: The user wanted to add a database, admin dashboard, and authentication to
  their sleep questionnaire app based on an SOW. I implemented these features,
  including a Prisma database model, API routes, and a simplified Next.js
  middleware-based authentication system for the admin dashboard.
overview: The user aimed to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire Application by
  integrating a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for data
  access, and an authentication system. After evaluating the existing codebase,
  I developed a plan to implement a  model using Prisma
  and NeonDB, create API endpoints for data submission and retrieval (including
  CSV export), and build a basic admin dashboard. A key decision involved
  simplifying the authentication from a custom HMAC-signed session to a more
  streamlined Next.js middleware-based approach, which uses a simple cookie for
  session management. This approach effectively protects the admin routes and
  API endpoints while keeping the implementation straightforward, aligning with
  the user's request for the simplest possible solution. The implementation
  included updating demographic fields in the questionnaire to match SOW
  requirements and providing clear instructions for database setup and
  migration.
